==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Will'''

#A [[diminutive]] of '''[[William]]'''.

Psychologically, the synthesis of the various internal principles. That synthesis is Will. 

According to certain esoteric doctrine, the only Will there is in the universe is what exoteric theology calls the “Will of God.” Yet the esoteric doctrine is a sharp variance from the exoteric fancy that any man has a will of his own, which he can oppose, to the will of God. When any man supposes himself to be possessed of such personal free will, he is suffering from a fundamental delusion.